@startuml Fabio_Investment_Flows_Architecture_Layers
!theme spacelab
title Fabio's Investment Flows - Architecture Layers & Dependencies

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1976D2
    FontColor #000000
}

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor #F3E5F5
    BorderColor #7B1FA2
    FontColor #000000
}

' Architecture Layers
package "Presentation Layer" {
    package "View Layer" {
        component [View Controllers] as VC
        component [Custom Views] as CV
        component [Table View Cells] as TVC
        component [Header Views] as HV
    }
    
    package "Presenter Layer" {
        component [Presenters] as P
        component [View Models] as VM
        component [Data Transformers] as DT
    }
    
    package "Interactor Layer" {
        component [Interactors] as I
        component [Business Logic] as BL
        component [Use Cases] as UC
    }
}

package "Navigation Layer" {
    component [Coordinators] as C
    component [Deep Link Resolvers] as DLR
    component [Navigation Manager] as NM
    component [Flow Controllers] as FC
}

package "Service Layer" {
    component [API Services] as AS
    component [Core Service] as CS
    component [Network Manager] as NM2
    component [Error Handler] as EH
    component [Request/Response Models] as RRM
}

package "Backend Template Layer" {
    component [StringToken System] as STS
    component [Metadata Processor] as MP
    component [Content Renderer] as CR
    component [Typography Engine] as TE
    component [Dynamic UI Builder] as DUB
}

package "Infrastructure Layer" {
    component [Dependency Injection] as DI
    component [Factory Pattern] as FP
    component [Service Locator] as SL
    component [Configuration] as CFG
}

package "Cross-Cutting Concerns" {
    component [Analytics & Tracking] as AT
    component [Security & Privacy] as SP
    component [Error Handling] as EH2
    component [Performance Monitoring] as PM
    component [Logging] as LOG
}

' External Dependencies
cloud "External Systems" {
    component [Backend API] as API
    component [Deep Link Handler] as DLH
    component [WebView Service] as WVS
    component [Analytics Service] as AS2
    component [Authentication Service] as AUTH
}

' Layer Dependencies
VC --> P : "depends on"
P --> I : "depends on"
I --> AS : "depends on"

C --> VC : "manages"
DLR --> C : "resolves to"
NM --> C : "manages"

AS --> CS : "uses"
CS --> API : "calls"

I --> STS : "processes"
STS --> MP : "parses"
MP --> CR : "renders"

DI --> VC : "injects into"
DI --> I : "injects into"
DI --> AS : "injects into"

AT --> I : "tracks"
SP --> I : "validates"
EH2 --> I : "handles"

' Backend Template Flow
note right of STS
  **StringToken Processing:**
  1. Parse value and style from backend
  2. Map to PurchaseTypograph enum
  3. Create StringWithTypograph objects
  4. Apply dynamic styling
end note

note right of MP
  **Metadata Processing:**
  1. Parse complex metadata structures
  2. Generate dynamic field mappings
  3. Create section-based layouts
  4. Support localization
end note

note right of CR
  **Content Rendering:**
  1. Build UI components from metadata
  2. Apply backend-controlled styling
  3. Support A/B testing variations
  4. Optimize performance
end note

' VIP Architecture Benefits
note left of VC
  **VIP Benefits:**
  - Clean separation of concerns
  - Testable architecture
  - Loose coupling
  - Single responsibility
  - Easy maintenance
end note

note left of P
  **Presenter Benefits:**
  - Data transformation
  - View model creation
  - UI logic isolation
  - State management
end note

note left of I
  **Interactor Benefits:**
  - Business logic isolation
  - Service coordination
  - Error handling
  - State management
end note

' System Architecture Benefits
note bottom
  **Overall System Benefits:**
  
  **Backend Template Architecture:**
  - Dynamic content without app updates
  - A/B testing capability
  - Rapid content iteration
  - Consistent styling across flows
  - Multi-language support
  
  **VIP Architecture:**
  - Clean, maintainable code
  - Easy testing and mocking
  - Clear separation of concerns
  - Scalable architecture
  
  **Navigation & Coordination:**
  - Flexible navigation patterns
  - Deep linking support
  - Flow management
  - Dependency injection
  
  **Infrastructure:**
  - Comprehensive error handling
  - Security and privacy protection
  - Performance monitoring
  - Analytics and tracking
end note

@enduml
